    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Festuca tenuis are skin irritations and burns, which are effectively treated with its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, reducing redness and promoting wound healing. Infertility in women is also improved by the plant's hormone-regulating properties, which balance estrogen levels and enhance ovulation. Additionally, Festuca tenuis has been shown to alleviate respiratory issues, such as bronchitis and asthma, due to its expectorant and bronchodilator effects, facilitating air passage and mucus clearance. The plant's antioxidant properties also make it an effective treatment for oxidative stress-related conditions, including neurodegenerative diseases like Alzheimer's and Parkinson's. Furthermore, Festuca tenuis has been used to treat gastrointestinal disorders, including ulcers and inflammatory bowel disease, by reducing inflammation and promoting the healing of the gastrointestinal tract.",
