    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Festuca tenuis are anti-inflammatory, which are attributed to the flavonoids present in this plant, thereby reducing inflammation and pain. The antioxidant properties of Festuca tenuis, mediated by saponins, protect cells from oxidative damage and promote overall health. This plant has also been found to exhibit antimicrobial activity, which is a result of the volatile oils it contains, thereby inhibiting the growth of various pathogens. Furthermore, Festuca tenuis has been reported to possess antidiabetic properties, likely due to the presence of phenolic compounds, which help regulate blood sugar levels. Additionally, the plant's antioxidant properties also contribute to its anti-aging effects, resulting from the ability of its bioactive compounds to neutralize free radicals and promote cellular regeneration.",
