    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Festuca tenuis are flavonoids, phenolic acids, and sesquiterpenes, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Flavonoids such as isorhapontigenin have been found to possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial activities, while phenolic acids like ferulic acid have been reported to exhibit antiseptic and antioxidant effects. Sesquiterpenes, including farnesol and \u03b2-caryophyllene, have been identified as potential anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory agents, with the ability to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and modulate the immune response. Additionally, the plant contains other bioactive compounds like lignans and coumarins, which have been shown to possess antibacterial and antifungal properties. These constituents are responsible for the plant's traditional uses in treating wounds, skin conditions, and respiratory infections, making it a valuable resource in folk medicine.",
