    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Festuca tenuis are festuca tea, infusion, festuca tincture, salve and decoction. Festuca tea is prepared by steeping dried Festuca tenuis leaves in boiling water to make a tea that may be used to treat digestive issues and promote relaxation. Festuca infusion involves steeping the leaves in cold water to create a more delicate flavor and is often used to reduce inflammation and improve respiratory function. Festuca tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the leaves in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin and is commonly used in homeopathic remedies for its antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. Festuca decoction involves simmering the leaves in water to extract its active compounds and is traditionally used to treat fever, cough and sore throats.",
