    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Festuca tenuis improperly are experience allergic reactions due to the presence of sesquiterpene lactones which can cause skin and respiratory issues in some individuals, exacerbate nausea as the plant's volatile oils may irritate the stomach lining, develops skin irritation from direct contact with the plant's sap, induce diarrhea due to the presence of saponins that can disrupt gut health, and trigger severe allergic reactions in people who are highly sensitive to the plant's compounds. These side effects are attributed to the plant's chemical composition, particularly the presence of sesquiterpene lactones and saponins, which can cause adverse reactions in some individuals. When used improperly, Festuca tenuis can release its volatile oils into the air, exacerbating respiratory issues. The plant's sap can also cause skin irritation in some individuals, particularly those with sensitive skin. It is essential to handle the plant with caution and avoid direct contact to minimize the risk of adverse reactions.",
